<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870702-0156 </DOCNO><HL> Service Corp. Offers to BuyCapital Southwest Division</HL><DD> 07/02/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CSWC SRVTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> WASHINGTON  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Service Corp. International said in a Securities and Exchange Commission filing that it offered to buy Capital Southwest Corp.'s 99.8% stake in Skylawn Corp. for $25 million. Service Corp. requested that Capital Southwest respond to its offer by Monday.    Skylawn, based in Hayward, Calif., owns and operates cemeteries, mausoleums and mortuaries. Houston-based Service Corp., which operates funeral homes and makes caskets, holds a 7.4% stake in Capital Southwest, representing 140,000 of the common shares outstanding.    Capital Southwest, a Dallas-based venture capital company, had no comment. </TEXT></DOC>